  1. To ensure that both the data, and the analysis are unique to each student, randomly sample about 2% of your data using a random 4-digit number as the seed to sample the data. Use 75% of the sampled data as the training set, and the rest as the test set (if needed). This should yield a training set of about 9000 and a test of about 3000.
# Set a random seed for reproducibility
set.seed(1234)

# Randomly sample about 2% of the rows from the dataset
sampled <- PUDL %>% 
  sample_frac(0.02)

# Split the sampled data into training and test sets

train<- sampled %>% 
  sample_frac(0.75)

test<- sampled %>%
    anti_join(train)
